cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with server allocation in a server farm that offers internet services. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the allocation of resources in a distributed system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a dynamic allocation policy to balance conflicting goals. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to maximize the quality of users' experience. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper considers the cost of running servers and aims to minimize it.
